    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.34-35_0001a" />
                <note type="curatorial">149-1</note>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                Skyrim Farm                    <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>        <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                    <lb/>
                Route 7
                    <lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.  
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Dec 15, 61</dateline> 
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>                
                <p>I'm thinking a lot of you and Stewart alone in that beautiful house, and I'm worrying too about Lucile. Connie wrote me that Lucile was getting along well, and I do hope she may soon be back with you.</p>
                
                <p>That is dear of you, good friend, to call your home my "second home". I've felt that way about it when I've been there.</p>
              
                <p>I've been through a strenuous time, and am just now
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.34-35_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    getting really rested. The affair at Lincoln was beautifully planned and worked out. Lucile's fine message about my Mona was read. A number of 
                    <hi rend="caps">VIP's</hi> took part in the affair.</p>
                
                <p>I <hi rend="underline">do</hi> want to hear something very encouraging about Lucile.</p>
                    <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John N.</signed>
                    </closer>
                
                    <postscript><p>I'm sure Perky wonders what has happened!</p></postscript>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">34</fw>
            </div1>
            
            
            
